WHAT IS MORE IMPORTANT, FAMILY OR FRIENDS?

When do you usually spend time with family?

How often do you spend time with friends?

“Walking with a friend in the dark is better than walking alone in the light .” “ Blood is thicker than water.”
What do these sayings mean? What do you think about these sayings?	

// Vocabulary
1. Significant (adj) /sɪɡˈnɪfɪkənt/: ​important or ​noticeable:
2. Inseparable (adj) / ɪnˈseprəbl/:  such good ​friends that they ​spend most of ​their ​time together, or (of two or more things) so ​closely ​connected that they cannot be ​considered separately:
3. Stand for (phrasal Verb) /stænd /fɔːr/
4. Kinship (n)/ˈkɪnʃɪp/:  the ​relationship between ​members of the same ​family
5. Companionship (n) /kəmˈpæniənʃɪp/
6. Acquaintance (n) /əˈkweɪntəns/: a ​person whom you ​know but do not ​know well 

// idioms
Be in favor of (phrase): support and agree with somebody/something
Know someone inside and out (idiom) : If you know someone inside and out, you know them very well.

// Structure: Can’t help
S + can’t help + but + V (inf.)+ O.

“Family is more important than friends.”
Do you agree or disagree with the above statement?
